<h2>Yes for Accessibility!</h2>
<p>Interact with the&nbsp;10 point checklist while reviewing a newly converted Word document. The links provide a guide to complete each checkpoint. Finally, click, "Yes" as each checkpoint is complete.</p>

<div style="height: 400px;">
<ol>
<li class="checklist">
Are <a href="https://www.csun.edu/universal-design-center/creating-accessible-word-2016-documents#A1">styles</a>&nbsp;used for title and section headers?
<span style="float: right;">
<input type="radio" checked="checked" value="n" name="number 1" /> No <input type="radio" value="y" name="number 1" /> Yes </span>
</li>
<li class="checklist">
Are&nbsp;<a href="https://www.csun.edu/universal-design-center/creating-accessible-word-2016-documents#A2">styles</a><span>&nbsp;used instead of selecting font size and effects?<span style="float: right;"><input type="radio" checked="checked" value="n" name="number 2" /> No <input type="radio" value="y" name="number 2" /> Yes </span>
</li>
<li class="checklist">
Are numbered&nbsp;<a href="https://www.csun.edu/universal-design-center/creating-accessible-word-2016-documents#A2">lists and bullets</a>&nbsp;used (when appropriate)?<span style="float: right;"><input type="radio" checked="checked" value="n" name="number 3" /> No <input type="radio" value="y" name="number 3" /> Yes </span>
</li>
<li class="checklist">
Do&nbsp;<a href="https://www.csun.edu/universal-design-center/creating-accessible-word-2016-documents#A3">images and objects</a><span>&nbsp;have meaningful alternative text (alt text)?<span style="float: right;"><input type="radio" checked="checked" value="n" name="number 4" /> No <input type="radio" value="y" name="number 4" /> Yes </span>
</li>
<li class="checklist">
Was&nbsp;<a href="https://www.csun.edu/universal-design-center/creating-accessible-word-2016-documents#A6">color contrast</a>&nbsp;considered?<span style="float: right;"><input type="radio" checked="checked" value="n" name="number 5" /> No <input type="radio" value="y" name="number 5" /> Yes </span>
</li>
<li class="checklist">
Are&nbsp;<a href="https://www.csun.edu/universal-design-center/creating-accessible-word-2016-documents#A4">tables</a>&nbsp;used to cross-reference information?<span style="float: right;"><input type="radio" checked="checked" value="n" name="number 6" /> No <input type="radio" value="y" name="number 6" /> Yes </span>
</li>
<li class="checklist">
Are&nbsp;<a href="https://www.csun.edu/universal-design-center/creating-accessible-word-2016-documents#A5">links</a>&nbsp;active and use meaningful link text?<span style="float: right;"><input type="radio" checked="checked" value="n" name="number 7" /> No <input type="radio" value="y" name="number 7" /> Yes </span>
</li>
<li class="checklist">
Are&nbsp;<a href="https://www.csun.edu/universal-design-center/creating-accessible-word-2016-documents#A20">columns</a>&nbsp;used to condense large amounts of information?<span style="float: right;"><input type="radio" checked="checked" value="n" name="number 8" /> No <input type="radio" value="y" name="number 8" /> Yes </span>
</li>
<li class="checklist">
Has the <a href="https://www.csun.edu/universal-design-center/creating-accessible-word-2016-documents#A7">Check Accessibility</a> tool&nbsp;been run?<span style="float: right;"><input type="radio" checked="checked" value="n" name="number 9" /> No <input type="radio" value="y" name="number 9" /> Yes </span>
</li>
<li class="checklist">
Has the document been <a href="https://www.csun.edu/universal-design-center/creating-accessible-word-2016-documents#A8">converted to a PDF</a>?<span style="float: right;"><input type="radio" checked="checked" value="n" name="number 10" /> No <input type="radio" value="y" name="number 10" /> Yes </span>
</li>
</ol></div>

<h3>Additional Considerations</h3>
<p>These remaining items provide additional accessibility consideration for Word Accessibility.</p>
<ul>
<li>Use a concise document file name that doesn't include spaces i.e. Word-Accessibility-Example.docx</li>
<li>A table of content is provided for longer documents (can be automatically created by using proper headers)</li>
<li>A document title and author are present</li>
<li>All comments are removed or have been turned off</li>
</ul>